==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Envelopment
<hw>En*vel"op*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>enveloppement</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of enveloping
or wrapping; an inclosing or covering on all sides.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which envelops or surrounds; an
envelop.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Envenime</ent>⟦br⟧
